about.summary: Sphinx needs extension for managing needs/requirements and specifications

name: sphinx-needs
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "sphinx-needs" %}
{% set version = "2.0.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/sphinx_needs-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cbb42e919b20cf758f6d0571709fe95ec08b3e2e8f386274ddd738e9e924ceb7

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - setuptools
    - poetry-core >=1.0.8
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.7.0
    - sphinx >=5.0
    - docutils >=0.15
    - matplotlib-base >=3.3.0
    - requests-file >=1.5.1,<2.0.0
    - requests >=2.25.1,<3.0.0
    - jsonschema >=3.2.0
    - sphinxcontrib-plantuml
    - sphinx-data-viewer >=0.1.1,<0.2.0
    - esbonio >=0.11.3

test:
  imports:
    - sphinx_needs
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://github.com/useblocks/sphinx-needs
  summary: Sphinx needs extension for managing needs/requirements and specifications
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - melund
